excerpt: Punta del Este is a seaside city and peninsula on the Atlantic Coast in the Maldonado Department of southeastern Uruguay. Starting as a small town, Punta del Este grew to become a resort for the Latin and North American jet set and tourists. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Punta del Este, located in southeastern Uruguay, started as a small town and has grown into a popular resort for the Latin and North American jet set. The city offers spectacular natural scenery with low vegetation and gentle hills. It is known for its international hospitality standards and extra tolerance towards the LGBTQ+ community, making it a comfortable destination for all travelers. Additionally, Punta del Este boasts glamorous beaches like La Barra and Chihuahua Beach.
name: Punta del Este
address: Maldonado Department, Uruguay

excerpt: No-frills beach offering scenic surrounds & strong currents, making it popular for surfers.
detail_description: Playa Brava is a no-frills beach known for its scenic surroundings and strong currents, making it a popular spot for surfers. One of its landmarks is the famous sculpture 'Los Dedos,' created by Chilean artist Mario Irarrazabal, which depicts a hand buried in the sand. Visitors can enjoy the nice beach and clean facilities, including free washrooms. The area offers good waves for surfing and a pleasant atmosphere to relax.
name: Playa Brava
address: Maldonado Department, Uruguay

excerpt: White sandy beach known for its surfing, sunbathing parking & seasonal lifeguards.
detail_description: La Barra is a charming coastal town known for its white sandy beaches, perfect for surfing and sunbathing. The area is characterized by its unique style and picturesque houses, as well as art galleries, antique shops, and a lively flea market. The iconic bridge of La Barra allows visitors to cross the Maldonado stream and is a symbol of the region's tourism. This laid-back surfer-magnet offers boutiques, bars, and stretches of sand.
name: La Barra
address: Maldonado Department, Uruguay

excerpt: Offering big waves & a sandy beach, this spot is a popular destination for surfers.
detail_description: Playa el Emir is a popular destination for surfers due to its big waves and sandy beach. It's part of a series of great spots that come alive during winter low pressure systems, making it the most rewarding time for surfers. The beach also features a shipwreck and offers beautiful views for leisurely walks along the promenade. Additionally, visitors can enjoy whale watching and take advantage of nearby amenities such as parking lots and easy access to the promenade.
name: Playa el Emir
address: Maldonado Department, Uruguay
